President Obama has nominated Sherry Moore Trafford and Judge Steven Michael Wellner to serve on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Sherry Moore Trafford has worked as a staff attorney in the Mental Health Division of the Public Defender Service for the District of Columbia since 2004. She has a J.D. from Yale Law School and a B.A. with honors from Indiana University. Judge Steven Michael Wellner is currently the Principal Administrative Law Judge for Unemployment Insurance Appeals for the District of Columbia Office of Administrative Hearings. Before that, he worked as a partner at Kirkland & Ellis LLP, focusing on environmental counseling for corporations. He has a J.D. from the University of Michigan and a B.A. with high distinction from the University of Virginia. President Obama expressed confidence that both nominees will serve on the bench with distinction.